				<p><b>Details:</b> These hacks use the :before element to add shapes behind your element, inheriting the background color you set in that row, column or module. You can customize the background color, gradient, or image in <b>Module or Row Settings > Content Tab > Background</b>.</p>
				<p>Note: These shapes will NOT show up on Internet Explorer or Microsoft Edge because these browsers don’t support the clip-path css property. Instead, it will just show the element without the shape.</p>
				<p><b>Add a Drop Shadow:</b> Box shadows settings don’t work on these shapes. Instead, add the filter CSS property to the <b>Element's Settings > Advanced tab > Custom CSS > Main Element Custom CSS</b>.<br />
				<pre style="font-family:monospace !important; padding:10px; background-color:#4e5764; color:#fff;">filter:drop-shadow(0px 5px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.2));<br />-webkit-filter:drop-shadow(0px 5px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.2));</pre></p>
